Label: haplotype member of
Definition: A relation between a protein complex and a haplotype, in which some parts of the protein complex are encoded by genes in the haplotype.

Label: serotype member of
Definition: A relation between a protein complex and a serotype, in which the protein complex belongs to the serotype by virtue of its disposition to bind with certain antibodies.

Label: is synthetic protein mutant of
Definition: A relationship between a protein that was designed as a variant and its naturally occurring template protein, where the synthesized variant has one or more defined differences - typically introduced to examine the impact of such variations on protein function.

Label: MHC gene
Definition: The region of a chromosome that codes for MHC molecules.
Example of Usage: The class II regions encoding for the DP, DQ, and DR molecules on human chromosome 6.

Label: MHC haplotype
Definition: A set of MHC alleles that is frequently inherited together.
Example of Usage: The mouse H-2-k class II haplotype is expressed in C3H mice.

Label: serotype
Definition: A pattern of antibody binding associated with certain material entities

Label: MHC serotype
Definition: A serotype identifying a specific group of MHC molecules.
Example of Usage: The human  HLA-A3 serotype includes HLA-A*03:01 and HLA-A*03:02.

Label: T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay
Parent: assay measuring binding of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

Label: MHC protein complex with haplotype
Definition: A protein complex that is a member of an MHC haplotype.
Example of Usage: The mouse H-2-Kk molecule belongs to the H-2-k haplotype.

Label: MHC protein complex with serotype
Definition: A protein complex that is a member of an MHC serotype.
Example of Usage: The human HLA-A*03:01 molecule is part of the HLA-A3 serotype.

Label: mutant MHC protein complex
Logic: ('is synthetic protein mutant of' some 'MHC protein complex')
Definition: A protein complex in which one or both chains has at least one amino acid residue altered from the wild type sequence.
Example of Usage: The HLA-B*08:01 B:I66A mutant protein has a single amino acid mutation in the B*08:01 chain at residue 166, where the wild type isoleucine was replaced with an alanine.

Label: Beta-2-microglobulin gene
Definition: The region of a chromosome that codes for Beta-2-microglobulin molecules.
